##<a id='who'></a>For Security Professionals and <%= vars.product_name %> Users

This guide explains how <%= vars.first_product_name  %> manages network access, roles and permissions, internal communications, container hardening, and other security issues. It is intended to give security professionals a complete view of <%= vars.product_name %> security, and to help all <%= vars.product_name %> users, not just the security experts, keep the platform secure.

In addition, this guide provides information about <%= vars.product_name %> compliance with published control standards and regulations such as [NIST Special Publication 800-53(r4)](https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/SpecialPublications/NIST.SP.800-53r4.pdf) and [GPDR](https://eugdpr.org/).

##<a id='cves'></a> Pivotal Security Processes and CVE Reports

Pivotal publishes security updates regularly in response to privately- and publicly-reported Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVEs).

* See the latest CVEs on the [Pivotal Application Security Team](https://pivotal.io/security) page.

* To learn about Pivotal's vulnerability reporting and responsible disclosure process, read [<%= vars.product_name %> Security Overview and Policy](./process/pcf-security.html).

* To learn about the testing, release and security lifecycle of <%= vars.product_name %>, see [<%= vars.product_name %> Testing, Release, and Security Lifecycle](./process/security-lifecycle.html).

